addRoom(string,string,string,uint256,boo.notice: This is to add a new room.

deleteReservation(uint256,uint256).notice: Delete a reservation. Is based off the rooms ID.

makePayment(uint256).details: Adds new payment to list. And sets wei or ether on contract.
makePayment(uint256).notice: This handles payments. Lodges a new payment into our smart contract data. In order to receive payment you must use the withdraw() function.

makeReservation(uint256,uint256,uint256,.details: Add new reservation to list.  The amount of wei is determined by the compiler.  Checks that room id exists.
makeReservation(uint256,uint256,uint256,.notice: This is to make a new reservation. The room is reserved by whoever made the call.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
